$interpreted: Naya: These clothes...whoever tailored them has got balls. This thin! Looks like it won't cover our butts, chest or thighs!
Naya: It's like we're not wearing anything at all. Are these really for the water?
Sharice: I...I think this is my family's fault. Or perhaps General Lucien had these custom made...
Sione: No. If you inspect them carefully, these are the perfect clothes for the water.
Sione: Although the tailor definitely had guts, they're tight and flexible. No matter what the activity, there will be no restrictions.
Sione: Water-resistant material will reduce the burden on the body. This is the most well-rounded style for water sports!
Sharice: Sione's got a point...
Naya: But won't wearing these outfits be embarrassing?
Angelia: If you really think about it, does it matter?
Naya: Angel, are you okay with this?
Angelia: There's no one we know here anyway. Plus, we're all women, so there's nothing to be embarrassed about.
Angelia: Naya, weren't you the one who said we shouldn't worry too much?
Hestia: Didn't you all say you wanted to change? What are you still doing here? If we don't get down to the beach, it's going to get dark!
Angelia: Okay, then I'll just pick this one with laced gauze!
Naya: Angel, you party pooper, I've had my eye on that one the whole time!
Angelia: Ooohh wah! The water's so cold!
Naya: Angel, watch my moves!
Angelia: Hehehe, I'll return the favor!
Hestia: Hey, let's do a swim race to that point over there.
Naya: Yeah! If we're testing physical strength, there's no way I'll lose.
Sharice: Your Majesty the Queen, please don't go where the water is too deep!
Angelia: Oh. I know...
Angelia: Sharice, here we're just normal friends, you don't need to be so formal when you address me.
Sharice: No, no. I'm just a petty soldier. If I am too informal...
Sione: There's a hole on the back of your swimsuit.
Sharice: Co-captain Sione, what are you doing!!
Angelia: When you see a shot, you've gotta take it!
Angelia: Hehe, if you can't accept it then you'd better strike back~

Sharice: ......
Just because I'm not attacking doesn't mean I'm just a poor little kitty-cat! I'll show you!
Sharice: Behold my power and DRINK!
Angelia: *whew*~ completely exhausted.
Naya: I never thought my swimming skills would be surpassed by Hestia...
Sione: She is half-fish, after all. Is it really that surprising?
Sharice: Sooo tired. I'm going to lay down on the shore...
Sharice: What's that!?
Hestia: Maple Lake Aqua Wolves!? Did it chase a Hungry Lake Mudpye and Floating Jellyfish down here?
Naya: Oh, great! Those wolves are biting our luggage!
Sharice: Our weapons aren't on us. What are we going to do?
Sione: All I've got is this toy...
Hestia: They said that they wanted to help!
Naya: All this stuff is a flimsy as a noodle! Will it be stable enough?
Naya: Ew...it's cold and sticky!
Sharice: It's wrapping around my body!
Angelia: Oh, no! They're coming our way!
Angelia: All that energy we used has come back!
Sione: Looking pretty good, let's go!
Naya: Hey, those wolves left already. You guys can get going!
Angelia: Sharice, what are you holding?
Sharice: I don't know. I just checked to see if my luggage was missing and found this thing deep in the car.
Sharice: All it does is gives off this glaring light, nothing else.
Sione: Seems like it's another water toy.
Sharice: Hmm...my mom and dad probably made a mistake.
Sharice: Whatever. Let's go rest under the umbrella!
